videos.description: Emmanuel Reed rumbles 55-yards deep into Kent State territory.
videos.headline: Reed's 55-yard gain puts Buffalo in red zone

videos.description: Emmanuel Reed's second touchdown run extends the lead for Buffalo in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Reed scores again to extend Buffalo's lead

videos.description: Dustin Crum and Kavious Price connect for a 75-yard TD pass to get Kent State on the board.
videos.headline: Crum and Price strike for TD

videos.description: Kobe Green blocks the punt to set up Buffalo in scoring position.
videos.headline: Green blocks Kent State's punt

videos.description: Emmanuel Reed's third rushing touchdown pushes the lead for Buffalo.
videos.headline: Reed's third TD extends Buffalo's lead

videos.description: QB Drew Anderson fools the Kent State defense for a 64-yard run in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Anderson gallops for 64-yard run

videos.description: Drew Anderson and Zac Lefebvre connect from 5-yards out to increase the lead for Buffalo.
videos.headline: Anderson's first TD pass extends the lead

videos.description: Anthony Johnson makes a tough over-the-shoulder catch for a 36-yard gain in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Anderson and Johnson connect for 36 yards

videos.description: George Bollas completes pass to Trey Harrell for 54 yards in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Kent State's Bollas passes it to Harrell for a big gain

videos.description: Tito Overton interception comes on a botched throw back pass.
videos.headline: Kent State throws interception on failed trick play

videos.description: Michael Reghi and Jerod Cherry break down Buffalo's powerful win in their MAC opener.
videos.headline: Buffalo's Reed impressive performance leads to a dominating win over Kent State
